  "id": "phekb-gout-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "gout",
  "name": "Gout - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying gout patients via Condition + MedicationRequest + Observation (urate). Path D captures asymptomatic hyperuricemia.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete gout patient population. Some patients have a coded gout diagnosis. Others have only allopurinol or colchicine prescriptions, and some have only a documented elevated urate without a formal gout diagnosis. Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis, medications, and urate labs — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all gout patients.",
    "broad": "Find all gout patients — by diagnosis, allopurinol/colchicine medications, or elevated urate (>7 mg/dL). Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run three queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|90560007 — gout dx. (2) MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|519,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|2683 — allopurinol+colchicine. (3) Observation?code=http://loinc.org|3084-1&value-quantity=gt7||mg/dL — elevated urate. Union the patient IDs."
  },
